### Super light
So, you want to go super light. Here is an example of a very light hike and fly setup

Paraglide - [U-turn EVEREST](http://www.u-turn.de/web/english/products/paragliders/everest) - 2.4kg
Harness - [Sky Country, Ascet LT](http://sky-country.com/ascet-lt/), 0.6kg
Reserve - [Sky Country SQ](http://sky-country.com/sq/) - 1.0kg
Helmet - [BD Vapor](https://www.blackdiamondequipment.com/en_CA/climbing-helmets/vapor-helmet-BD620215_cfg.html) - 0.2kg, $140USD
Backpack - Montano 45L

Total weight: 4.5kg

My current hike and fly setup:
Paraglide - [AirDesign Super Easy light](https://ad-gliders.com/project/eazy-2-superlight-sexyhandling/?lang=en) - 3.5kg
Harness - [SupAir, Radical 3 with airbag](https://www.supair.com/en/produit/radical3/) - 1.5kg
Reserve - Sup Air, Solo - 1.2kg
Helmet - Bike helmet, 0.3kg
Backpack - reversed harness

Total weight: 6.5kg
